&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Deal Desk Operations Manager, you will own the end-to-end commercial execution process across quoting, approvals, and contract execution globally. You will play a critical role in enabling efficient, scalable, and compliant deal execution, ensuring processes are simple, transparent, and aligned to company policies and best practices. &amp;nbsp;Instrumental to your success will be your ability to optimize deal workflows, enforce pricing and governance guidelines, and continuously improve systems and processes to support efficient execution at scale.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Instrumental in your success will be your management for driving deal velocity and enhancement of systems and processes for enforcing pricing and governance guidelines and deliver a high quality selling experience across quoting, approvals and contract execution. &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will partner cross-functionally with key stakeholders to ensure pricing structures support efficient deal execution and align with company policies across teams. Your ability to identify and lead process improvements while collaborating effectively, will be key to strengthening D2L’s quoting function. You thrive in a fast-paced environment, motivated by solving problems and driving operational excellence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a team player, with the perfect balance of organization and attention to detail that allows you to get work done in a timely and accurate manner. &amp;nbsp; Analytical with strong communication are some of your top qualities, and you are at your best working in a rapidly changing environment. &amp;nbsp;You will use these attributes to contribute to an already exceptional Finance team!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
